===2010 Census===
As of the [[2010 United States census]], there were 377 people living in the town. 99.2% were [[African American]] and 0.8% [[White American|White]].

As of the [[census]]<ref name="GR2">{{cite web |url=https://www.census.gov |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]] |accessdate=January 31, 2008 |title=U.S. Census website }}</ref> of 2000, there were 325 people, 110 households, and 74 families living in the town. The population density was {{convert|3,663.5|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. There were 123 housing units at an average density of {{convert|1,386.5|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of the town was 98.2% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 1.5% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]] and 0.3% from two or more races.

There were 110 households, out of which 40.9% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 14.5% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 45.5% had a female householder with no husband present, and 32.7% were non-families. 29.1% of all households were made up of individuals, and 14.5% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.95 and the average family size was 3.65.

In the town, the population was spread out, with 41.8% under the age of 18, 9.2% from 18 to 24, 28.3% from 25 to 44, 10.8% from 45 to 64, and 9.8% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 23 years. For every 100 females, there were 92.9 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 77.5 males.

The median income for a household in the town was $11,882, and the median income for a family was $12,327. Males had a median income of $17,625 versus $13,250 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the town was $4,840. About 55.6% of families and 55.3% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 63.9% of those under age 18 and 73.5% of those age 65 or over.

